<p>If you are using PHP, you can use this function to search for and remove // /* type comments from the JSON string before parsing it into an object/array:</p>

<pre><code>function json_clean_decode($json, $assoc = true, $depth = 512, $options = 0) {
       // search and remove comments like /* */ and //
       $json = preg_replace("#(/\*([^*]|[\r\n]|(\*+([^*/]|[\r\n])))*\*+/)|([\s\t]//.*)|(^//.*)#", '', $json);

       if(version_compare(phpversion(), '5.4.0', '&gt;=')) {
           $json = json_decode($json, $assoc, $depth, $options);
       }
       elseif(version_compare(phpversion(), '5.3.0', '&gt;=')) {
           $json = json_decode($json, $assoc, $depth);
       }
       else {
           $json = json_decode($json, $assoc);
       }

       return $json;
   }
</code></pre>

<p>Hope this helps!</p>
